{"type":"message","id":"da8f44b6","parentId":"2f76335e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T01:54:00.066Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full file tree. Let me download all the files via the GitLab API. I'll create a script to download them all.\n\nKey files I need first:\n1. package.json (already have)\n2. vite.config.js\n3. index.html\n4. src/main.jsx\n5. src/App.jsx\n6. src/configs/axiosInterceptor.js (this will have the API URL)\n7. .env.example or any env file (if it exists)\n\nLet me download the key files first, then the rest.\n\nThe project has 465 files. I need to download them all. Let me write a script to do this.","thinkingSignature":"23fa95b740bac8a8483de3abfbdfdbe55094694b08e09a2d478d08b5579a3b21"},{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! 465 files found. Let me download the entire repo via the GitLab API.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sp9is54p8g7r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend\nTOKEN=\"glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65\"\nPROJECT=77055851\nBRANCH=\"develop\"\nBASE_URL=\"https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/${PROJECT}/repository/files\"\n\n# Download all files from the tree\ncat /tmp/dtlx_tree.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json, urllib.request, os, base64\n\ntoken = 'glpat-c_N4qQVxbcktRro-S5rdwGM6MQpvOjEKdTpoZDBsYg8.01.170axqn65'\nproject_id = '77055851'\nbranch = 'develop'\n\ndata = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfiles = [d for d in data if d['type'] == 'blob']\n\nbase_dir = '/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend'\n\nfor f in files:\n    path = f['path']\n    local_path = os.path.join(base_dir, path)\n    os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(local_path), exist_ok=True)\n    \n    url = f'https://gitlab.com/api/v4/projects/{project_id}/repository/files/{urllib.request.quote(path, safe=\\\"\\\")}/raw?ref={branch}'\n    \n    try:\n        req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={'PRIVATE-TOKEN': token})\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=30) as resp:\n            content = resp.read()\n            with open(local_path, 'wb') as out:\n                out.write(content)\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f'ERROR: {path} -> {e}')\n\nprint(f'Downloaded {len(files)} files')\n\"","yieldMs":120000,"timeout":300}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":4606,"output":598,"cacheRead":26533,"cacheWrite":428,"totalTokens":32165,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776131610788,"responseId":"062cd11b9870da515523da0fdd073fe7"}}
